Definition: original (prolonged) אֲדֹנִיָּהוּ ; from {{h113}} and {{h3050}}; lord (i.e. worshipper) of Jah; Adonijah, the name of three Israelites; Adonijah.
from {{h113}} and {{h6664}}; lord of justice; Adoni-Tsedek, a Canaanitish king; Adonizedec.
from the same as {{h113}} (in the sense of strength); a basis (of a building, a column, etc.); foundation, socket.
intensive from the same as {{h134}}; firm; Addan, an Israelite; Addan.
an emphatic form of {{h113}}; the Lord (used as a proper name of God only); (my) Lord.
from {{h113}} and {{h966}}; lord of Bezek; Adoni-Bezek; a Canaanitish king; Adonibezek.
or (fully) אֱדוֹמִי ; patronymic from {{h123}}; See {{h726}}.; an Edomite, or descendants from (or inhabitants of) Edom; Edomite.
plural of {{h121}}; red spots; Adummim, a pass in Palestine; Adummim.
or (fully) אַדְמוֹנִי ; from {{h119}}; reddish (of the hair or the complexion); red, ruddy.
probably of Persian derivation; Admatha, a Persian nobleman; Admatha.
(Aramaic) probably of Persian origin; quickly or carefully; diligently.
(Aramaic) from the same as {{h147}}, and {{h1505}}; a chief diviner, or astrologer; judge.
from {{h113}} and {{h7311}}; lord of height; Adoniram, an Israelite; Adoniram.
from {{h113}} and {{h6965}}; lord of rising (i.e. high); Adonikam, the name of one or two Israelites; Adonikam.
probably of foreign derivation; perhaps meaning fire; Adar, the 12th Hebrew month; Adar.
a primitive root; to expand, i.e. be great or (figuratively) magnificent; (become) glorious, honourable.
from {{h142}}; amplitude, i.e. (concrete) a mantle; also (figuratively) splendor; goodly, robe.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h143}}; Adar.
(Aramaic) intensive, from a root corresponding to {{h142}}; ample, i.e. a threshing-floor; threshingfloor.
intensive from {{h142}}; ample; Addar, a place in Palestine; also an Israelite; Addar.
from {{h127}}; earthy; Adami, a place in Palestine; Adami.
the same as {{h127}}; Adamah, a place in Palestine; Adamah.
from {{h119}}; soil (from its general redness); country, earth, ground, husband(-man) (-ry), land.
contracted for {{h127}}; earthy; Admah, a place near the Dead Sea; Admah.
reduplicated from {{h119}}; reddish; (somewhat) reddish.
from {{h119}}; redness, i.e. the ruby, garnet, or some other red gem; sardius.
or (fully) אֱדוֹם ; from {{h122}}; red (see Genesis 25:25); Edom, the elder twin-brother of Jacob; hence the region (Idumaea) occupied by him; Edom, Edomites, Idumea.
from {{h119}}; rosy; red, ruddy.
the same as {{h120}}; Adam the name of the first man, also of a place in Palestine; Adam.
from {{h119}}; ruddy i.e. a human being (an individual or the species, mankind, etc.); × another,   hypocrite,   common sort, × low, man (mean, of low degree), person.
of Persian derivation; Adalja, a son of Haman; Adalia.
to show blood (in the face), i.e. flush or turn rosy; be (dyed, made) red (ruddy).
of uncertain derivation; Iddo, an Israelite; Iddo.
or (shortened) אָדֹן; from an unused root (meaning to rule); sovereign, i.e. controller (human or divine); lord, master, owner. Compare also names beginning with 'Adoni-'.
probably from {{h109}} (in the sense of chastisement) and {{h410}}; disciplined of God; Adbeel, a son of Ishmael; Adbeel.
probably an orthographical variation for {{h2301}}; Adad (or Hadad), an Edomite; Hadad.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; then (of time); now, that time, then.
from {{h142}}; wide or (generally) large; figuratively, powerful; excellent, famous, gallant, glorious, goodly, lordly, mighty(-ier one), noble, principal, worthy.
probably intensive for {{h113}}; powerful; Addon, apparently an Israelite; Addon.
dual from {{h142}} (in the sense of eminence); double mound; Adorajim, a place in Palestine; Adoraim.
of Aramaic derivation and probably meaning soldier of Merodak; Evil-Merodak, a Babylonian king; Evil-merodach.
from an unused root meaning to twist, i.e. (by implication) be strong; the body (as being rolled together); also powerful; mighty, strength.
feminine of {{h188}}; woe.
from an unused root (meaning to be perverse); (figuratively) silly; fool(-ish) (man).
from {{h191}}; silly, foolish; hence (morally) impious; foolish.
or (shortened), אֻלָם ; from {{h481}} (in the sense of tying); a vestibule (as bound to the building); porch.
or (shortened) אֻלַי; from {{h176}}; if not; hence perhaps; if so be, may be, peradventure, unless.
of Persian derivation; the Ulai (or Eulaeus), a river of Persia; Ulai.
appar, from {{h481}} (in the sense of dumbness); solitary; Ulam, the name of two Israelites; Ulam.
apparently a variation of {{h194}}; however or on the contrary; as for, but, howbeit, in very deed, surely, truly, wherefore.
from the same as {{h191}}; silliness; folly, foolishly(-ness).
probably from {{h183}}; desirous; Evi, a Midianitish chief; Evi.
probably from {{h183}} (in the sense of crying out after); lamentation; also interjectionally Oh!; alas, woe.
from {{h183}}; longing; desire, lust after, pleasure.
a primitive root; to extend or mark out; point out.
of uncertain derivation; Uzal, a son of Joktan; Uzal.
perhaps by permutation for {{h5813}}, strong; Uzai, an Israelite; Uzai.
from an unused root meaning to rake together; a poker (for turning or gathering embers); (fire-) brand.
or (shortened) אֻבָל ; from {{h2986}} (in the sense of {{h2988}}); a stream; river.
a primitive root; to wish for; covet, (greatly) desire, be desirous, long, lust (after).
or (shortened) אֹדוֹת (only thus in the plural); from the same as {{h181}}; turnings (i.e. occasions); (adverb) on account of; (be-) cause, concerning, sake.
of uncertain derivation; a basin; charger.
(Aramaic) of Persian origin; an epistle (as carried by a state courier or postman); letter.
feminine of {{h104}}; an epistle; letter.
from {{h1640}} (in the sense of grasping); the clenched hand; fist.
probably from {{h5059}}; a bowl (as pounded out hollow); basin, cup, goblet.
a primitive root; to harvest; gather.
probably from {{h5062}} (through the idea of impending); a cover or heap; i.e.; (only plural) wings of an army, or crowds of troops; bands.
a primitive root; to languish; grieve.
from the same as {{h181}} (in the sense of enveloping); a fog; mist, vapor.
in form a feminine of {{h168}}, but in fact for אׇהֳלָהּ; from {{h168}}; her tent (i.e. idolatrous sanctuary); Oholah, a symbolic name for Samaria; Aholah.
from {{h168}} and {{h1}}; tent of (his) father; Oholiab, an Israelite; Aholiab.
(similarly with {{h170}}) for אׇהֳלִיבָהּ ; from {{h168}}; my tent (is) in her; Oholibah, a symbolic name for Judah; Aholibah.
from {{h168}} and {{h1116}}; tent of (the) height; Oholibamah, a wife of Esau; Aholibamah.
or (feminine) אֲהָלוֹת (only used thus in the plural); of foreign origin; aloe wood (i.e. sticks); (tree of lign-) aloes.
of uncertain derivation; Aharon, the brother of Moses; Aaron.

presumed to be the 'constructive' or genitival form of אַו ; short for {{h185}}; desire (and so probably in Proverbs 31:4); hence (by way of alternative) or, also if; also, and, either, if, at the least, × nor, or, otherwise, then, whether.
from {{h176}} and {{h410}}; wish of God; Uel, and Israelite; Uel.

from the same as {{h1}} (apparently through the idea of prattling a father's name); properly, a mumble, i.e. a water-skin (from its hollow sound); hence a necromancer (ventriloquist, as from a jar); bottle, familiar spirit.
probably from {{h56}}; mournful; Obil, an Ishmaelite; Obil.
probably of foreign origin; Ahava, a river of Babylonia; Ahava.
apparently a primitive word expressing pain exclamatorily; Oh!; ah, alas.
from an unused root meaning to be united; unity; Ohad, an Israelite; Ohad.
feminine of {{h158}} and meaning the same; love.
a denominative from {{h168}}; to tent; pitch (remove) a tent.
a primitive root; to be clear; shine.
apparently an orthographical variation for {{h346}}; where; I will be (Hosea 13:10,14) (which is often the rendering of the same Hebrew form from {{h1961}}).
from the same as {{h161}}; united; Ehud, the name of two or three Israelites; Ehud.
the same as {{h168}}; Ohel, an Israelite; Ohel.
from {{h166}}; a tent (as clearly conspicuous from a distance); covering, (dwelling) (place), home, tabernacle, tent.
from {{h157}}; affection (in a good or a bad sense); love(-r).
from {{h156}}; meaning the same as {{h158}}; love.
a primitive root; to tread out (grain); thresh.
or אָהֵב ; a primitive root; to have affection for (sexually or otherwise); (be-) love(-d, -ly, -r), like, friend.
from the equivalent of {{h153}}; mighty; Edrei, the name of two places in Palestine; Edrei.
feminine of {{h117}}; ; also the same as {{h145}}; something ample (as a large vine, a wide dress); garment, glory, goodly, mantle, robe.
from {{h142}} and {{h4428}}; splendor of (the) king; Adrammelek, the name of an Assyrian idol, also of a son of Sennacherib; Adrammelech.
(Aramaic) an orthographical variation for {{h1872}}; an arm, i.e. (figuratively) power; force.
of Persian origin; a daric or Persian coin; dram.
contracted for {{h141}}; Adoram (or Adoniram), an Israelite; Adoram.
